                                Preamble

 The FFP (Freedom For People) License is a free and permissive license
 intended to maximize human freedom by ensuring that software,
 documentation, art, media, data, and other copyrightable works remain
 available for anyone to use, study, modify, and share.

 This License grants broad permission to use, copy, modify, distribute,
 and sell the Work, while requiring that recipients receive a copy of
 this License and that copyright and attribution notices are preserved.

 This License also includes a patent license grant from Contributors,
 and it protects the commons by terminating patent rights granted under
 this License if a recipient initiates patent litigation alleging that
 the Work infringes a patent.

 The Work is provided without warranty, and the Licensor and Contributors
 disclaim liability for damages.

 The precise terms and conditions follow.

