 0. Definitions.

  "This License" refers to version 1.0 of the FFP (Freedom For People)
 License.

  "Copyright" also means copyright-like laws that apply to other kinds of
 works, such as semiconductor masks.

  "Work" means the original work of authorship, including software,
 documentation, hardware design files, art, data, or media, that is
 initially distributed under this License by the Licensor.

  "Contribution" means any original work of authorship, including any
 modifications or additions to the Work or Derivative Works thereof,
 that is intentionally submitted for inclusion in the Work by a
 Contributor, whether submitted by an individual or on behalf of a legal
 entity.

  "Derivative Work" means any work based upon the Work or Contributions,
 such as a modification, translation, adaptation, or compilation, which
 would require permission under applicable copyright law.

  "Distribute" (or "Distribution") means to provide, transfer, publish,
 or convey a copy of the Work, Contributions, or Derivative Works to a
 third party, whether in source form, binary form, or any other form.

  Mere interaction with a user through a computer network, without
 transfer of a copy, is not Distribution.

  "You" (or "Your") means the individual or legal entity exercising
 permissions granted by this License.

  "Licensor" means the copyright holder(s) or entity authorized by the
 copyright holder(s) that initially distributes the Work under this
 License.

  "Contributor" means the Licensor and any other individual or legal
 entity on behalf of whom a Contribution has been submitted or
 distributed under this License.

