                  HOW TO APPLY THE FFP LICENSE TO YOUR WORK

 To apply the FFP (Freedom For People) License to your Work, follow the
 steps below.

 It is recommended that you:

   1. Place a full copy of the FFP (Freedom For People) License text in
      a file named "LICENSE" (or "COPYING") in the top-level directory of
      your Work.

   2. Add the notice below to the main README file and/or the header of
      important source files.

   3. Ensure that all copyright notices, license notices, and attribution
      notices included in the Work are preserved in any redistributed
      copies or Derivative Works, as required by the License.

 You may replace the bracketed placeholders with your own information.

    Copyright (C) [YEAR] [FULL NAME OF LICENSOR OR ORGANIZATION]

    This Work is licensed under the FFP (Freedom For People) License,
    Version 1.0.

    A copy of this License must be included in the LICENSE file
    distributed with this Work.

    You may also obtain a copy of the License at:
    https://github.com/druvx13/FFP

    THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
    OR IMPLIED.

 If your Work includes interactive user interfaces, it is recommended
 (but not required) that you display an appropriate notice stating that
 the Work is licensed under the FFP License and that it comes without
 warranty.

                      END OF APPLICATION GUIDE
